meta-licheepizero-adb
=====================

Yocto/OpenEmbedded meta-layer that enables **Android Debug Bridge (ADB) over USB**
on the **Lichee Pi Zero** (Allwinner V3s SoC) and **Lichee Pi Zero Dock**.

This layer provides the kernel configuration, device-tree patch, U-Boot config,
and init script needed to make the board's USB port act as a peripheral running
`adbd`, so a host PC can connect via `adb shell`, `adb push/pull`, etc.

Dependencies
============

Required layers (kirkstone branch):

  URI: https://github.com/yoctoproject/poky.git
  branch: kirkstone

  URI: https://github.com/openembedded/meta-openembedded.git
  branch: kirkstone
  layers: meta-oe, meta-networking, meta-python

  URI: https://github.com/licheepizero/meta-licheepizero.git
  branch: kirkstone

  URI: https://github.com/openembedded/meta-qt5.git (optional, for Qt)

Dependencies (runtime): `android-tools-adbd` and `android-tools-conf-configfs`
from meta-openembedded/meta-oe provide the `adbd` binary and USB gadget setup
script (`/usr/bin/android-gadget-setup`).


Adding the layer to your build
==============================

Run:

  bitbake-layers add-layer meta-licheepizero-adb

In your `local.conf`, ensure the following are set:

  ## Target machine (provided by meta-licheepizero)
  MACHINE = "licheepizero-dock"

  ## Use configfs-based ADB (not the deprecated g_android module)
  PREFERRED_PROVIDER_android-tools-conf = "android-tools-conf-configfs"

  ## Install the ADB daemon and init script
  IMAGE_INSTALL:append = " android-tools-adbd adbd"


Layer contents
==============

recipes-core/adbd/
  Init script (`/etc/init.d/adbd`) that starts `adbd` at boot and binds the
  USB gadget to the UDC controller.

recipes-kernel/linux/
  - `adb.cfg` — kernel config fragment enabling USB gadget, configfs, FunctionFS,
    and the Allwinner V3s MUSB controller. Disables USB Ethernet gadget (conflicts
    with ADB).
  - `0001-v3s-force-usb-peripheral.patch` — DTS patch that sets USB OTG `dr_mode`
    to `"peripheral"` instead of `"otg"`, forcing the port into gadget mode.

recipes-uboot/u-boot/
  - `bootdelay.cfg` — sets `CONFIG_BOOTDELAY=0` for headless boot (no serial
    input required).

